==English==

===Noun===
'''caprice'''
# an impulsive seemingly unmotivated notion or action 
# an unpredictable or sudden condition, change, or series of changes
# a disposition to be impulsive
# an impulsive change of mind

===Etymology===
French, from Italian ''[[capriccio]]'', from ''caporiccio'', meaning (fright, sudden start ): ''[[capo]]'', head (from Latin ''[[caput]]'') + ''[[riccio]]'', curly (from Latin ''[[ericius]]'' (meaning hedgehog)

